{
  "_comment": [
    "County reference data for QSO party analysis.",
    "",
    "Structure: one entry per host state, keyed by state abbreviation.",
    "Each entry has:",
    "  format    - how the county exchange is encoded in Cabrillo logs:",
    "                '3letter'  - 3-char abbrev (e.g. ALB, ERI) used by NYQP, most single-state parties",
    "                '4letter'  - 4-char abbrev (e.g. ALBA, ERIE) used by some parties",
    "                'SSCCC'    - state prefix + county abbrev (e.g. NYALB) used by multi-state parties",
    "  counties  - dict of exchange-code -> full county name",
    "",
    "When adding a new state:",
    "  1. Add its entry here with the correct format and county list",
    "  2. Add a config/[party]_[year].json pointing to it via host_state",
    "  3. Add a GeoJSON boundaries file to reference/[state]_counties.json",
    "  4. The pipeline will pick up the county list automatically via host_state in the config"
  ],

